    "recap_headline": "Eastern Michigan Athletics",
    "recap_text": "YPSILANTI, Mich. (EMUEagles.com) \u2013\nThe Eastern Michigan University baseball team fell to the University of Akron, 7-3, in a Mid-American Conference series opener Friday, March 20, at Oestrike Stadium.\nEastern took a 1-0 lead in the bottom of the first but was outscored 7-2 the remainder of the game.\nEastern's\nJohn Carmichael\n(Destrehan, Ill./Destrehan/McClennan C.C.)\ngot the start for the Eagles and went five innings, allowing two runs off six hits with three strikeouts and two walks. Akron's Brady Bowen (2-0) was credited with the win while Carmichael (0-4) was tagged with the loss.\nHow it Happened\nEastern Michigan struck first, taking a 1-0 lead in the bottom of the first inning when\nBruce Jellison\n(Hartland, Mich./Hartland/Wabash Valley)\nsingled to score\nTJ Williams\n(Racine, Wis./Racine Horlick/Kansas)\n.\nAkron tied the game in the third inning and took a 2-1 lead in the fourth on a solo home run from Easton Amundson. The Zips added two more runs in the top of the seventh to extend their lead to 4-1.\nThe Eagles mounted a two-out rally in the bottom of the seventh. Jellison delivered his second RBI single of the day, followed by an RBI double from freshman\nDemir Heidelberg\n(Homewood, Ill./Homewood Flossmor)\nthat cut the deficit to 4-3. However, Akron's offense responded by scoring one run in the eighth and two in the ninth to secure the victory.\nGame Notes\n\u00bb Eastern's record went to 4-17 (0-7 MAC) and Akron's improved to 10-10 (4-3 MAC).\n\u00bb\nBruce Jellison\nrecorded two hits in five at-bats for his first multi-hit game of the year, adding two RBI. He has now recorded a hit in five of the last six games. The two RBI marked his fourth and fifth of the season and his second multi-RBI\u00a0game of the season, most recently doing so Feb. 14, at Little Rock.\n\u00bb\nDemir Heidelberg\nrecorded the second multi-hit game of his career with a 2-for-4 day at the plate with one RBI, the second of his collegiate tenure. Heidelberg previously knocked two hits at Miami, March 7, and drove in the first RBI of his career against the RedHawks the next day, March 8.\n\u00bb\nTJ Williams\nknocked a pair of hits for his team-leading seventh multi-hit game. Williams leads the team with 21 hits this season, ranking ninth in the MAC.\n\u00bb\nJohn Carmichael\nwent at least five innings for the fourth time this season, doing so in four of his six starts. He allowed just two earned runs, tying for his season low originally set at Austin Peay, Feb. 20, 2026.\n\u00bb\nCole Egan\n(Pittsburgh, Pa./West Allegheny/George Mason)\ntied a season high with three strikeouts.\n\u00bb\nBen Schechterman\n(Aurora, Ohio/Aurora/Ohio State)\nworked two walks for the second time in his career and for the\u00a0first time this season.\nHistorical Notes\n\u00bb The Eagles met Akron for the 78th time. Eastern holds a 48-30 record all-time against the Zips and a 10-14 mark when facing it at Oestrike Stadium since 1999.\nUp Next\nThe Eagles and Zips will do it again tomorrow, Friday, March 21, at\u00a03 p.m. for the second of three games.\nFollow Us\nKeep up with all things Eastern baseball by following the team on X\n@EMU_Baseball\n, and on Instagram\n@emu_baseball\n.",
